Code.Name: strip

Code.Name: stick
Code.Description: A unit of count defining the number of sticks (stick: slender and often cylindrical piece of a substance).

Code.Name: stick, cigarette
Code.Description: A unit of count defining the number of cigarettes in the smallest unit for stock-taking and/or duty computation.

Code.Name: standard litre

Code.Name: ton (US) or short ton (UK/US)

Code.Name: straw

Code.Name: skein

Code.Name: shipment

Code.Name: syringe

Code.Name: telecommunication line in service

Code.Name: thousand piece

Code.Name: metric ton, including container

Code.Name: metric ton, including inner packaging
Code.Description: A unit of mass defining the number of metric tons of a product, including its inner packaging materials.

Code.Name: tonne kilometre
Code.Description: A unit of information typically used for billing purposes, expressed as the number of tonnes (metric tons) moved over a distance of one kilometre.

Code.Name: kilogram of imported meat, less offal

Code.Name: tonne (metric ton)

Code.Name: ten pack

Code.Name: teeth per inch

Code.Name: ten pair
Code.Description: A unit of count defining the number of pairs in multiples of 10 (pair: item described by two's).

Code.Name: thousand cubic metre per day

Code.Name: ten set

Code.Name: ten thousand sticks
Code.Description: A unit of count defining the number of sticks in multiples of 10000 (stick: slender and often cylindrical piece of a substance).

Code.Name: treatment

Code.Name: tablet

Code.Name: telecommunication line in service average

Code.Name: telecommunication port

Code.Name: percent volume

Code.Name: wet ton
